The Obama Administration has announced a new initiative called Clean Energy Savings for All, which aims to increase access to solar energy and promote energy efficiency in low- and moderate-income communities. The initiative includes partnerships between various government departments, such as Energy, Housing and Urban Development, and Agriculture, as well as private and philanthropic sectors. The key components of the initiative include: releasing new guidance to unlock residential Property-Assessed Clean Energy financing, developing a Community Solar Challenge to increase solar deployment in low-income communities, making it easier for low-income households to access funding for renewable energy investments, launching the Solar Training Network to create a more inclusive workforce, bringing stakeholders together to share best practices, and securing commitments from housing authorities, power companies, and organizations to invest in solar energy projects. The initiative aims to reduce energy bills, empower consumers, and create cleaner communities.